    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hello all!\r\nI have a py file in my project file which size is 1.7mb.\r\nWhile compiling first a .c file of size 40.4mb is produced.\r\nWhile processing compilation takes 6.5 gb RAM and then fails when RAM and SWAP are exhausted.\r\nIs there a way to compile such files? For example by automatically breaking them to several .c files parts?",
    "closed_at": "2020-07-10T15:20:03Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
            "body": "Support questions are better asked on [the cython-users mailing list](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/cython-users).\r\n\r\nThe answer is probably roughly:\r\n1. buy more RAM.\r\n2. reduce the C optimization level\r\n3. split the py files into multiple submodules.",
